76561198024280675,Not Recommended,227060,9230162,"Posted: 23 February, 2014",all,Bodie,"Has a lot of potential but there are a few things which make this a very clunky game at the moment.Firstly the dialog box is too big, as well as that information panel which pops up when you highlight something.  For a 32inch 1080p monitor I kind of expect a little more leg-room buts its all taken up with these boxes.Secondly the mouse scrolling is not very friendly.  I'm used to games with a static scroll rate, and find myself pushing my cursor way past the sides, which the game interprets as 'I want to scroll FASTER!!!'  Pretty annoying.A wider field of view would be helpful.Needs some extra work on the AI.  One of my legion units split up somehow and one side got attacked which made them all rally, even though they were a good distance apart.Also finding my attack/move orders are often denied because of inaccessible terrain.  Like if I click on a cliff face the units will deny my order.  Would be better if they went to the closest point possible instead of just rejecting the order.I'm going to say no to recommending this game, only because its just not ready, no-where near ready (and the developers told me to be critical).  Buy it if you like the genre but expect some frustration."
